==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heteropathy
<hw>Het`er*op"a*thy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Heteropathic</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>That mode of
treating diseases, by which a morbid condition is removed by inducing an
opposite morbid condition to supplant it; allopathy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heteropelmous</ent>⟦br⟧
